sub_questions: How to identify serous tumor samples from Histologic_type column?
Should excluded cases be filtered out?
Should analysis include only tumor samples or also normal samples?
How to handle missing Age values?

format_notes: Histologic_type column contains tumor type classifications
Case_excluded column indicates whether case should be included in analysis
Proteomics_Tumor_Normal column distinguishes tumor from normal samples

constraints: Age must be non-null for average calculation
derived_filters: Filter for serous histologic type: check if 'serous' appears in Histologic_type value
Exclude cases marked as excluded in Case_excluded column
Include only tumor samples, not normal tissue samples
output_format_requirements: Single numeric value representing mean age
Round to appropriate decimal places (1-2 decimal places)
Report sample size (number of serous tumor samples included)
